Props to TwistedGears and Soulless for suggesting changes, others in chat for rubber-stamping it, cyrus013 and pooryoric for making a post Sorts made back in 2011 for giving the inspiration for this article.

This article is sort of intended to function as a continuation of 181's story, but I tried to make it so that you don't have to have any knowledge of 181 for the article to work.

Doesidea?

Sortof.


There is definitely the possibility that 181 is in solitary confinement for its own good, and solitary confinement at the Foundation is the safest place to be in 181's lifetime. There's also any number of other possibilities  you get the picture. Krupin, however, is very paranoid and very self-centered, so when he looked through 181's documentation, he interpreted it as writing on the wall and decided to do whatever it takes to get the same treatment.

Only time can tell if he was wise in doing so.






